\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 So far, this evaluation had resulted in gaining a point of strength and three points each of agility and endurance with attendant gains of 30 vitality and 23 stamina. That seemed pretty good so far, but made him wonder what was up next.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The Guide spoke up before he could ask. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Your gains so far have met expectations. The next cycle will focus on strength through the lifting, carrying and dragging of dead weight. The first step of the evaluation will be a series of deadlifts to establish your maximum lifting capability. The second step will be lifting and carrying a large weighted object a distance of 20 meters. This, too, will be repeated until the object becomes too heavy to carry the full distance. The final step will be dragging an object with a drag line attached. The object will grow heavier every meter it is dragged. The test will be complete when you can no longer move the object.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Two hours are allocated to complete this evaluation, however you may rest no more than 15 minutes between tests and once all three tests are complete you may use any remaining time as a rest period, though no questions will be answered until the full cycle is complete.\u8221\'94 The Guide paused. \u8220\'93I would recommend meditation between tests to maximize recovery in your case.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marcus nodded and settled into a brief meditation to prepare for the first test. }}